<pre><code>import javax.swing.JOptionPane;  public class Palindrome {     public static void main(String[] args) {         String letters[];         String word = "Level", results = "";         int i, j;         String w = word.toLowerCase();         letters = w.split("");         i = 1;         j = letters.length - 1;         while ((letters[i].equals(letters[j])) &amp;&amp; (i &lt; j)) {             i += 1;             j -= 1;         }         if (i &lt; j)             results = word + " is not a palindrome.";         else             results = word + " is a palindrome.";         JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null, results);     } } </code></pre>  <p>Can anyone explain why after splitting the String <code>w</code> the first element of array <code>letters</code> is <code>""</code> and not <code>"l"</code>? Instead that letters on index 1.</p>